\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Microeconomics
\series default
 is, basically, a theory of 
\series bold
decisions
\series default
.
 It studies how households and consumers make fundamental economic decisions
 on: what to buy, how much to work, etc.
 The idea to put an analytical framework to analyze this logic.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the background of each decision, there's always some scarcity (i.e limited
 budget, even when a big one).
 Each decision involves a tradeoff.
 (Buying more of something - can buy less of something else; work more -
 less leisure time; save more - consume less, etc).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\series bold
tradeoff
\series default
 is the underlying reason for the theory (it's not needed when there's no
 scarcity).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The main paradigm is that rational people always try to maximize their interests
 / utility.
 It doesn't mean that people are always rational in reality, it just means
 that people 
\series bold
try
\series default
 (there are many reasons for them not to succeed: lack of time / information,
 cognitive biases, etc), and they are rational to some extent, and systematicall
y do try to make the best decision for themselves.
\end_layout

